---
description: Do not stop at intermediate milestones when user requests full-scope delivery
alwaysApply: false
---

# Requested Scope Delivery No Mid-Stop

- When user asks to continue / finish / deliver / complete, treat as full requested-scope delivery; intermediate milestones are not stopping points.
- Intermediate milestones include: completing one slice, producing a review, updating task docs, passing partial tests.
- Keep going unless one of these is true:
  - Acceptance criteria for the requested scope are fully met
  - User explicitly narrowed scope (`review-only`, `docs-only`, `stop after this slice`)
  - Real blocker: conflicting user edits, ambiguous ownership across frozen boundaries, missing credentials/resources, repeated failures with multiple valid product decisions
- `no-commit` does not narrow delivery scope; it only skips the commit step.
- When pausing for a blocker, state which completion condition is unmet and why safe continuation is blocked.
